which xact properties does crash recovery enforce

isolated.
dualbility

what is the force/no-force policy (buffer management)? 
	when we commit we force the page to be flushed to the disk.

what is the steal/no-steal policy (buffer management)
	no-steal
		

When should a log record be flushed to the disk (write-ahead logging)
	if we're waiting for something to be flushed, so we can undo
	When we commit, so we can redo

why do we need checkpoints in the logging system?
	So we don't have to check the entire log. we therefor make checkpoints when we commit, and things are flushed to the disk.

